ANALYSIS.TITLE: TCGA/ICGC PanCancer Donor-Level Variant Calling for Participant ITNET-0911
ANALYSIS.DESCRIPTION: [Description EMBL]: This is the variant calling for specimen 911T from donor ITNET-0911. The results consist of one or more VCF files plus optional tar.gz files that contain additional file types. This uses the EMBLPancancerStr workflow, version 1.0.3 available at https://registry.hub.docker.com/u/pancancer/pcawg-delly-workflow/builds_history/153343/. This workflow can be created from source, see https://github.com/ICGC-TCGA-PanCancer/pcawg_delly_workflow. For a complete change log see CHANGELOG.md. Note the 'ANALYSIS_TYPE' is 'REFERENCE_ASSEMBLY' but a better term to describe this analysis is 'SEQUENCE_VARIATION' as defined by the EGA's SRA 1.5 schema. Please note the reference used for alignment was hs37d, see ftp://ftp.1000genomes.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/ftp/technical/reference/phase2_reference_assembly_sequence/README_human_reference_20110707 for more information. Briefly this is the integrated reference sequence from the GRCh37 primary assembly (chromosomal plus unlocalized and unplaced contigs), the rCRS mitochondrial sequence (AC:NC_012920), Human herpesvirus 4 type 1 (AC:NC_007605) and the concatenated decoy sequences (hs37d5cs.fa.gz). Variant calls may not be present for all contigs in this reference. [Description DKFZ]: This is the variant calling for specimen 911T from donor ITNET-0911.
